cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the classification of cervical cells based on their appearance and morphology using convolutional neural networks. It may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it involves the retrieval of relevant information from cervical cell images. Additionally, it could be classified under Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it uses deep learning techniques to classify the cells. Multimedia (cs.MM) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with image analysis. Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks for classification.
